Task
An array of numbers from 1 to n
Write a createArray function that takes a number n as an argument and returns an array containing natural numbers from 1 to a given number n: [1, 2, 3, ...., n].
If n = 0, return an empty array [].
Example:
• the createArray (3) function must return [1, 2, 3];
• the createArray (7) function must return [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7];
• the createArray (1) function must return [1];
• the createArray (0) function must return [].

Solution
function createArray (n) {
 let arr = [];
  for (let i = 1; i <= n; i ++) {
  arr.push (i);
 }
 return arr;
}
